<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07813</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROMOTING BREASTFEEDING PRACTICES IN THE PHILIPPINES AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Declares breastfeeding as basic human rights; Mandates institutions adopting rooming-in and promoting breastfeeding to provide equipment, facilities, and supplies for breast milk collection, storage and utilization; Provides for the education, marketing of breastmilk substitutes, breastmilk supplements and related products. </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Breastfeeding Practices Act” </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C., MACEDA, EDWARD VERA PEREZ, MARTINEZ, ERIC M., SANDOVAL, FEDERICO &quot;RICKY&quot; II S., MALAPITAN, DALE &quot;ALONG&quot; R., OLIVAREZ, ERIC L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-08-08)</td><td>2. Vergara (000 2018-08-30)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>